full description:
About The Role
At Cainthus, we work together on talented cross-disciplinary teams to develop original computer vision-enabled products. As a Senior Software Engineer (Full-Stack), your technical leadership, creativity and experience in delivering complex products, will improve the operations of dairy farms globally. You will work side by side with world-class computer vision engineers and data scientists in small, multidisciplinary teams solving high impact problems that have global importance in Agritech and the food chain.
This role is full-stack, with the emphasis on the front-end and the API layer.
What you’ll do

Contribute to the Cainthus cloud solution;
Write elegant, well-crafted code (full stack with a focus on the front end);
Implement user experiences using React and in APIs in Python;
Advise and mentor other developers in engineering best practices;
Help drive the underlying technology stack and the implementation methodology;
Drive performance tuning and automation.
What we’re looking for
Required Skills

Minimum 4 years experience in similar roles;
Deep and demonstrable experience in Python;
Demonstrable commercial Javascript experience in Web or Mobile context (React or React Native);
Solid commercial experience in designing and building robust, scalable APIs and web applications in a Linux ecosystem;
Demonstrated ownership of full end to end testing;
Experience with building Docker container-based systems: familiar with orchestration platforms such as Kubernetes, AWS ECS, AWS EKS;
Experience using CI/CD pipeline (CircleCI, Jenkins, Code Deploy, etc.) for faster software delivery;
Excellent communication and problem-solving skills;
An inherent drive to tackle problems, collaborate with others, and mentor team members in a fast-paced, high-growth, ever-changing startup environment;
Strong Database knowledge, ideally with PostgreSQL, MySQL or DynamoDB;
A track record of solving complex problems with secure, elegant solutions.


Nice to Have

Experience configuring DAGs for Airflow;
Experience with time-series data or stream processing using Kinesis;
Experience with IoT devices and edge processing;
Experience with the Django framework.
Value you’ll deliver

Enabling and providing secure, resilient, portable, and efficient end-to-end solutions;
Empowering customers with efficient and elegant user interfaces;
Empowering development teams with efficient self-service cloud & containerised solutions, growing agility and increasing the pace of innovation;
Reducing development team operational overhead by evaluating, exploring, recommending and enabling managed cloud services;
Emphasis on writing clear, readable, testable, deployable and monitored code for server-side applications.
What we offer
Joining our team has its rewards. You will be working in Dogpatch Labs, a unique start-up community located in the historic CHQ Building in the heart of Dublin Digital Docklands. Here, you will have the opportunity to attend different events and meetups hosted by the tech community. Our benefits include:

Fully paid Group Health Cover for you and your immediate family;
Pension Scheme with 5% company matching;
25 days paid holidays per year (21 days flexible and 4 set company days);
Generous ESOP Scheme;
Flexible Wellness Benefit;
Family-Friendly Benefits;
Sim card linked to Cainthus business plan;
Bike to Work and Tax Saver schemes;
Management approved education and career development support.
About Us
We are a growing computer vision startup based in Dublin. We are a blend of computer vision specialists, engineers, designers, and data scientists, all from diverse backgrounds. We’re passionate about transforming farming through the use of our technology. We believe in taking ownership and want to be accountable for the work we do. We value transparency. We work together in agile multi-disciplinary teams and collaborate closely with a group of dairy farmers who ensure that our work has a meaningful impact on their farms. We love learning from each other, solving challenging problems and having fun along the way.
